# stable diffusion is deep learning technique to generate text to image. 
# It is a type of generative model that uses a diffusion process to create high-quality images from textual descriptions.
#  The model is trained on a large dataset of images and their corresponding text descriptions, allowing it to learn the relationship between the two modalities.
#  When given a text prompt, the stable diffusion model can generate an image that matches the description, making it a powerful tool for creative applications such as art generation, design, and content creation.

# stable diffusion is based on the concept of diffusion, which is a process that gradually transforms a simple noise distribution into a complex data distribution.
# The model consists of a series of layers that iteratively refine the generated image, starting from random noise and gradually adding details until it produces a final image that matches the input text description.
# The training process involves optimizing the model to minimize the difference between the generated images and the real images in the training dataset, using techniques such as adversarial training and variational inference.
